sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD), where a total volume of 20,647 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 2.1 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 51% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.0 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $217.50 strike put option expiring August 23, 2019, with 3,988 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 398,800 underlying shares of HD.
